Eventually Laurence decided to start the day – always a little arbitrary after a sleepless night – and washed his face and dressed.&nbsp; Staring into the small mirror, he saw a little vein in his left eye and wondered why there was not a red line across half his vision, then he did something he had not done in years – he closed one eye and opened the other, then switched, magically shifting his nose from side to side…&nbsp; Then he felt odd, foolish, and imagined Lord Cerbes and a flock of solicitors spiraling out of the sun to peck and peck…</span>
